Hi,

we are trying to make a push to one of our repos git@bitbucket.org:myaccount/myrepo.git

And get the following problem during push operation on a new branch:

{code}
#!bash

! [remote rejected] dev/performance-improvements -> dev/performance-improvements (failed to lock)
error: failed to push some refs to &#x27;ssh://git@bitbucket.org:myaccount/myrepo.git&#x27;
{code}

The syntax for deleting a git branch on a remote server is as follows:

{code}
#!bash

git remote -v
#copy the {branch-name} from the returned list
git push {repo_url} :{branch-name}
{code}

The essentially tells the remote git, match up my local branch (nothing on the left of the :) with the remote branch {branch-name} effectively removing the remote branch. There should probably be a way to do this on the site as well.
